verses.text_plain: I love the Lord, because he hath heard my voice and my supplications.
verses.verse_html: 1I love the Lord, because he hath heard my voice and my supplications.

verses.text_plain: Because he hath inclined his ear unto me, therefore will I call upon him as long as I live.
verses.verse_html:
2Because he hath inclined his ear unto me, therefore will I call upon him as long as I live. ▼
▼ as long…: Heb. in my days

tokens.text: unto me, therefore will I call

footnotes.body_text: ▼ as long…: Heb. in my days
footnotes.body_html: ▼ as long…: Heb. in my days

verses.text_plain: The sorrows of death compassed me, and the pains of hell gat hold upon me: I found trouble and sorrow.
verses.verse_html:
3The sorrows of death compassed me, and the pains of hell gat hold upon me: I found trouble and sorrow. ▼
▼ gat…: Heb. found me

footnotes.body_html: ▼ gat…: Heb. found me

verses.text_plain: Then called I upon the name of the Lord; O Lord, I beseech thee, deliver my soul.
verses.verse_html: 4Then called I upon the name of the Lord; O Lord, I beseech thee, deliver my soul.

verses.text_plain: Gracious is the Lord, and righteous; yea, our God is merciful.
verses.verse_html: 5Gracious is the Lord, and righteous; yea, our God is merciful.

verses.text_plain: The Lord preserveth the simple: I was brought low, and he helped me.
verses.verse_html: 6The Lord preserveth the simple: I was brought low, and he helped me.

verses.text_plain: Return unto thy rest, O my soul; for the Lord hath dealt bountifully with thee.
verses.verse_html: 7Return unto thy rest, O my soul; for the Lord hath dealt bountifully with thee.

verses.text_plain: For thou hast delivered my soul from death, mine eyes from tears, and my feet from falling.
verses.verse_html: 8For thou hast delivered my soul from death, mine eyes from tears, and my feet from falling.

verses.text_plain: I will walk before the Lord in the land of the living.
verses.verse_html: 9I will walk before the Lord in the land of the living.

verses.text_plain: I believed, therefore have I spoken: I was greatly afflicted:
verses.verse_html: 10I believed, therefore have I spoken: I was greatly afflicted:

verses.text_plain: I said in my haste, All men are liars.
verses.verse_html: 11I said in my haste, All men are liars.

verses.text_plain: What shall I render unto the Lord for all his benefits toward me?
verses.verse_html: 12What shall I render unto the Lord for all his benefits toward me?

verses.text_plain: I will take the cup of salvation, and call upon the name of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 13I will take the cup of salvation, and call upon the name of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: I will pay my vows unto the Lord now in the presence of all his people.
verses.verse_html: 14I will pay my vows unto the Lord now in the presence of all his people.

tokens.text: now in the presence of all his people

verses.text_plain: Precious in the sight of the Lord is the death of his saints.
verses.verse_html: 15Precious in the sight of the Lord is the death of his saints.

verses.text_plain: O Lord, truly I am thy servant; I am thy servant, and the son of thine handmaid: thou hast loosed my bonds.
verses.verse_html: 16O Lord, truly I am thy servant; I am thy servant, and the son of thine handmaid: thou hast loosed my bonds.

verses.text_plain: I will offer to thee the sacrifice of thanksgiving, and will call upon the name of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 17I will offer to thee the sacrifice of thanksgiving, and will call upon the name of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: I will pay my vows unto the Lord now in the presence of all his people,
verses.verse_html: 18I will pay my vows unto the Lord now in the presence of all his people,

tokens.text: now in the presence of all his people

verses.text_plain: In the courts of the Lord’s house, in the midst of thee, O Jerusalem. Praise ye the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 19In the courts of the Lord’s house, in the midst of thee, O Jerusalem. Praise ye the Lord.
